The paper presents a novel approach to resource analysis that is driven by the result of a termination analysis. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category, which deals with the use of logic and formal methods in computer science. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of CoFloCo and PUBS as CRS solvers, which are tools commonly used in program analysis and verification, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the complexity and termination of programs, which are topics commonly studied in Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of C Integer programs, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Systems and Networking (cs.SY) sub-category.
